# ============================================================================
# RestoFlow — application (CLIENT) environment (EXAMPLE — placeholders only)
# RF-013 — Supabase project bootstrap + environments + secrets
#
# These are the BUILD-TIME values the Flutter apps (apps/pos, apps/kds,
# apps/dashboard, apps/admin) need to reach a Supabase environment. Copy to
# `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in real values, OR pass them via
# `--dart-define` / `--dart-define-from-file` in CI.
#
# NOTE: actually WIRING these values into the apps happens in a LATER ticket.
# RF-013 only establishes the environment + secret-handling structure.
#
# WIRED DART-DEFINE NAMES (what the apps actually read at build time): the Flutter
# apps consume `RESTOFLOW_SUPABASE_URL` and `RESTOFLOW_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` (plus
# `RESTOFLOW_DEMO_MODE`, default true) via `--dart-define`. The generic
# SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_ANON_KEY names below are the human template; map them to
# the RESTOFLOW_-prefixed dart-defines when configuring a build or a hosted deploy.
# For the hosted Supabase/Vercel setup and env-var checklist, see docs/DEPLOYMENT.md.
#
# OPTIONAL (RF-LIVE-002 — public URLs, never secrets; leave unset to auto-derive):
#   RESTOFLOW_AUTH_REDIRECT_URL  overrides the sign-up email-confirmation redirect.
#                                Unset = derive from the runtime web origin (prod +
#                                preview). Set only for a custom domain.
#   RESTOFLOW_DASHBOARD_URL      the hosted Dashboard URL the Admin app's "open the
#                                Dashboard" link points at. Unset = local dev URL.
#
# WHAT BELONGS HERE (safe to ship to clients)
#   SUPABASE_URL        the project URL — a public endpoint, not a secret.
#   SUPABASE_ANON_KEY   the anon / publishable key — SAFE for clients. It is
#                       RLS-gated and carries no elevated privileges.
#
# WHAT MUST *NEVER* APPEAR HERE OR IN ANY CLIENT BUILD
#   (SECURITY REQUIREMENT — DECISION D-011): the service_role key, the database
#   password, or any "*service_role*" / "sb_secret_*" credential. Those are
#   SERVER-SIDE ONLY. A leaked service-role key bypasses RLS entirely and breaks
#   tenant isolation (RISK R-003, CRITICAL). It belongs only in server-side
#   config / a secrets manager — see supabase/.env.example and supabase/README.md.
# ============================================================================

# ---- Active environment selector: local | staging | production ------------
RESTOFLOW_ENV=local

# ---- local / dev  (fill from `supabase status` after `supabase start`) -----
SUPABASE_URL=YOUR_SUPABASE_DEV_URL
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR_SUPABASE_DEV_ANON_KEY

# ---- staging  (remote project) --------------------------------------------
# SUPABASE_STAGING_URL=YOUR_SUPABASE_STAGING_URL
# SUPABASE_STAGING_ANON_KEY=YOUR_SUPABASE_STAGING_ANON_KEY

# ---- production  (remote project) -----------------------------------------
# SUPABASE_PROD_URL=YOUR_SUPABASE_PROD_URL
# SUPABASE_PROD_ANON_KEY=YOUR_SUPABASE_PROD_ANON_KEY
